EU to Take All Necessary Steps to Underpin Banks, Barroso Says

-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 
2011-10-06T10:45:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/eu-to-take-all-necessary-steps-to-underpin-banks-barroso-says.html
European governments will do
“everything necessary” to stabilize the banking system,
European Commission President  Jose Barroso  said.  “We are determined to do everything necessary to ensure
that  Europe ’s banks are able to play their essential role in
lending,” Barroso said at a press conference with Finnish Prime
Minister  Jyrki Katainen  in Brussels today. “Recapitalization
efforts are well under way.”  Barroso added: “Close coordination at European level is
essential.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James G. Neuger at 
 jneuger@bloomberg.net  